Commentary Text: T Natarajan to Gaikwad, out Caught by Bhuvneshwar!! Heartbreak for Gaikwad, has been dismissed for 99, puts his head down in agony, doesn't want to go, but has to walk back to the dug-out, gets a lot of pats on his back from the SRH fielders, but what a knock this has been. This was short and this was wide of off, on another day, Gaikwad would have flayed it over backward point - but he's on 99, the nerves are jingling and he attempts the cute placement, rides the bounce and dabs it straight down Bhuvneshwar's throat at backward point. As soft as it gets. Gaikwad c Bhuvneshwar b T Natarajan 99(57) [4s-6 6s-6]

Commentary Text: Umran Malik to Gaikwad, FOUR, Umran Malik goes full and Gaikwad drills it straight down the ground. Commentary Text: Mukesh Choudhary to Tripathi, out Caught by Simarjeet Singh!! Two in two for Mukesh and he's on a hat-trick - catching practice at short third man, banged in short and just outside off - Rahul was shaping for the upper-cut as he arched back slightly, but in doing so, he was cramped for space, ran off the face of the bat and straight down Simarjeet's throat. Mukesh is chuffed to bits, this is a big wicket and CSK end the batting powerplay in some style. Tripathi c Simarjeet Singh b Mukesh Choudhary 0(1)

Commentary Text: Mukesh Choudhary to Abhishek Sharma, out Caught by Pretorius!! Mukesh has his man, will feel much better after that missed chance, it's Pretorius and the big man made this look easy. Pace off on this short delivery from Mukesh, pushed it wide of off as well and made Abhishek drag the lofted pull - was looking to go over mid-wicket, but spooned high off the bat and lobbed to the left of long-on. Pretorius made ground and clasped a reverse-cupped catch, right in front of his chest. Abhishek Sharma c Pretorius b Mukesh Choudhary 39(24) [4s-5 6s-1]
